#. type: Title =
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Actions"
msgstr "Acciones"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:2
msgid "You can manage actions on your clients in a number of different ways:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:3
msgid ""
"You can schedule automated recurring actions to apply the highstate or an "
"arbitrary set of custom states to clients on a specified schedule."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:4
msgid ""
"You can apply recurring actions to individual clients, to all clients in a "
"system group, or to an entire organization."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:5
msgid ""
"You can set actions to be performed in a particular order by creating action "
"chains."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:6
msgid ""
"Action chains can be created and edited ahead of time, and scheduled to run "
"at a time that suits you."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:7
msgid ""
"You can also perform remote commands on one or more of your Salt clients."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:8
msgid ""
"Remote commands allows you to issue commands to individual Salt clients, or "
"to all clients that match a search term."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:9
#, no-wrap
msgid "Recurring Actions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:10
msgid ""
"You can apply recurring actions on individual Salt clients, to a system "
"group, or to all clients in an organization."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:11
msgid ""
"Currently, {productname} supports the following action types as recurring "
"actions:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:12
msgid "[parameter]``Highstate:`` Execute the highstate."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:13
msgid ""
"[parameter]``Custom state:`` Execute a set of custom states. A custom state "
"can be either an internal state provided by {productname}, or a "
"configuration channel created by a user."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:14
msgid ""
"For more information about configuration channels, see xref:client-"
"configuration:configuration-management.adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:15
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Creating a New Recurring Action"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:16
msgid ""
"To apply a recurring action to an individual client, navigate to "
"[guimenu]``Systems``, click the client to configure schedules for, and "
"navigate to the [guimenu]``Recurring Actions`` tab."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:17
msgid ""
"To apply a recurring action to a system group, navigate to menu:"
"Systems[System Groups], select the group to configure schedules for, and "
"navigate to [guimenu]``Recurring Actions`` tab."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:18
msgid "Click btn:[Create]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:19
msgid "Select an action type from the [guimenu]``Action Type`` dropdown."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:20
msgid "Type a name for the new schedule."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:21
msgid "Choose the frequency of the recurring action:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:22
msgid "[guimenu]``Hourly:`` Type the minute of each hour."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:23
msgid ""
"For example, [parameter]``15`` runs the action at fifteen minutes past every "
"hour."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:24
msgid "[guimenu]``Daily:`` Select the time of each day."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:25
msgid ""
"For example, [parameter]``01:00`` runs the action at 0100 every day, in the "
"timezone of the {productname} Server."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:26
msgid ""
"[guimenu]``Weekly:`` Select the day of the week and the time of the day, to "
"execute the action every week at the specified time."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:27
msgid ""
"[guimenu]``Monthly:`` Select the day of the month and the time of the day, "
"to execute the action every month at the specified time."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:28
msgid ""
"[guimenu]``Custom Quartz format:`` For more detailed options, enter a custom "
"quartz string."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:29
msgid ""
"For example, to run a recurring action at 0215 every Saturday of every "
"month, enter:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:30
#, no-wrap
msgid "0 15 2 ? * 7\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:31
msgid ""
"OPTIONAL: Toggle the [guimenu]``Test mode`` switch on to run the schedule in "
"test mode."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:32
msgid ""
"For actions of type [parameter]``Custom state``, select the states from the "
"list of available states and click btn:[Save Changes]. This will only save "
"the current state selection and not the schedule."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:33
msgid ""
"In the next pane, drag and drop the selected states to put them in the "
"execution order and click btn:[Confirm]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:34
msgid ""
"Click btn:[Create Schedule] to save, and see the complete list of existing "
"schedules."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:35
msgid ""
"Organization Administrators can set and edit recurring actions for all "
"clients in the organization.  Navigate to menu:Home[My Organization > "
"Recurring Actions] to see all recurring actions that apply to the entire "
"organization."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:36
msgid ""
"{productname} Administrators can set and edit recurring actions for all "
"clients in all organizations.  Navigate to menu:Admin[Organizations], select "
"the organization to manage, and navigate to the menu:States[Recurring "
"Actions] tab."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:37
#, no-wrap
msgid "Action Chains"
msgstr "Cadenas de acción"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:38
msgid ""
"If you need to perform a number of sequential actions on your clients, you "
"can create an action chain to ensure the order is respected."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:39
msgid ""
"By default, most clients execute an action as soon as the command is "
"issued.  In some case, actions take a long time, which could mean that "
"actions issued afterwards fail.  For example, if you instruct a client to "
"reboot, then issue a second command, the second action could fail because "
"the reboot is still occurring.  To ensure that actions occur in the correct "
"order, use action chains."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:40
msgid ""
"For transactional update systems, an action chain is executed inside a "
"single snapshot, until there is a reboot action.  This can cause some "
"limitations."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/actions.adoc:41
msgid ""
"For more information, see xref:client-configuration:clients-slemicro.adoc[] "
"and xref:client-configuration:clients-opensuseleapmicro.adoc[]."
