#. type: Title =
#: modules/administration/pages/iss.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Inter-Server Synchronization - Version 1"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/iss.adoc:2
#: modules/administration/pages/iss_intro.adoc:4
msgid ""
"Starting with {productname} 5.0, the Inter-Server Synchronization (Version "
"1) feature will be deprecated and subsequently removed in future versions."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/iss.adoc:3
msgid ""
"If you have more than one {productname} installation, you need to ensure "
"that they stay aligned on content and permissions.  Inter-Server "
"Synchronization (ISS) allows you to connect two or more {productname} "
"Servers and keep them up-to-date."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/iss.adoc:4
msgid ""
"To set up ISS version 1, you need to define one {productname} Server as a "
"master, with the other as a slave.  If conflicting configurations exist, the "
"system prioritizes the master configuration."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/iss.adoc:5
msgid ""
"ISS Masters are masters only because they have slaves attached to them.  "
"This means that you need to set up the ISS Master first, by defining its "
"slaves.  You can then set up the ISS Slaves, by attaching them to a master."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: modules/administration/pages/iss.adoc:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Setting up an ISS Master"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/iss.adoc:7
msgid ""
"In the {productname} {webui}, navigate to menu:Admin[ISS Configuration > "
"Master Setup], and click btn:[Add new slave]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/iss.adoc:8
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``Edit Slave Details`` dialog, provide these details for the "
"ISS Master's first slave:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/iss.adoc:9
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``Slave Fully Qualified Domain Name`` field, enter the FQDN "
"of the ISS Slave."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/iss.adoc:10
msgid "For example: [systemitem]``server2.example.com``."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/iss.adoc:11
msgid ""
"Check the [guimenu]``Allow Slave to Sync?`` checkbox to enable the slave to "
"synchronize with the master."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/iss.adoc:12
msgid ""
"Check the [guimenu]``Sync All Orgs to Slave?`` checkbox to synchronize all "
"organizations to this slave."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/iss.adoc:13
msgid "Click btn:[Create] to add the ISS slave."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/iss.adoc:14
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``Allow Export of the Selected Organizations`` section, "
"check the organizations you want to allow this slave to export to the "
"master, and click btn:[Allow Orgs]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/iss.adoc:15
msgid ""
"Before you set up the ISS Slave, you need to ensure you have the appropriate "
"CA certificate."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: modules/administration/pages/iss.adoc:16
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Copying the Master CA Certificate to an ISS Slave"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/iss.adoc:17
msgid ""
"On the ISS Master, locate the CA Certificate at ``/srv/www/htdocs/pub/RHN-"
"ORG-TRUSTED-SSL-CERT`` and create a copy that can be transferred to the "
"ISS Slave."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/iss.adoc:18
msgid ""
"On the ISS Slave, save the CA certificate file to the ``/etc/pki/trust/"
"anchors/`` directory."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/iss.adoc:19
msgid "When you have copied the certificate, you can set up the ISS Slave."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: modules/administration/pages/iss.adoc:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Setting up an ISS Slave"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/iss.adoc:21
msgid ""
"In the {productname} {webui}, navigate to menu:Admin[ISS Configuration > "
"Slave Setup], and click btn:[Add new master]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/iss.adoc:22
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``Details for new Master`` dialog, provide these details for "
"the server to use as the ISS master:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/iss.adoc:23
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``Master Fully Qualified Domain Name`` field, enter the FQDN "
"of the ISS Master for this slave."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/iss.adoc:24
msgid "For example: ``server1.example.com``."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/iss.adoc:25
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``Filename of this Master's CA Certificate`` field, enter "
"the absolute path to the CA certificate on the ISS master."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/iss.adoc:26
msgid "This should be ``/etc/pki/trust/anchors/RHN-ORG-TRUSTED-SSL-CERT``."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/iss.adoc:27
msgid "Click btn:[Add new master] to add the ISS Slave to this master."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: modules/administration/pages/iss.adoc:28
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Completing ISS Setup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/iss.adoc:29
msgid ""
"At the command prompt on the ISS Slave, synchronize with the ISS Master:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/iss.adoc:30
#, no-wrap
msgid "mgr-inter-sync\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/iss.adoc:31
msgid "OPTIONAL: To synchronize a single channel, use this command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/iss.adoc:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "mgr-inter-sync -c <channel-name>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/iss.adoc:33
msgid ""
"In the {productname} {webui}, navigate to menu:Admin[ISS Configuration > "
"Configure Master-to-Slave Mappings] and select the organizations you want to "
"synchronize."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: modules/administration/pages/iss_intro.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Inter-Server Synchronization"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/iss_intro.adoc:2
#: modules/administration/pages/iss_v2.adoc:2
msgid ""
"If you have more than one {productname} installation, you will need to copy "
"contents between servers.  Inter-Server Synchronization (ISS) allows you to "
"export data from one server (source) and import it on another (target) "
"server.  This is useful for hub deployment scenarios or disconnected setups."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/iss_intro.adoc:3
msgid ""
"With the version 2 ISS implementation {suse} removed the master/slave "
"notion.  Contents can be exported and imported in any direction between any "
"{productname} server."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: modules/administration/pages/iss_v2.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Inter-Server Synchronization - Version 2"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/iss_v2.adoc:3
msgid ""
"With the version 2 ISS implementation {suse} removed the master/slave "
"notion.  Contents can be exported and imported in any direction between any "
"{productname} server."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/administration/pages/iss_v2.adoc:4
#, no-wrap
msgid "Install ISS Packages"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/iss_v2.adoc:5
msgid ""
"To use ISS you need to install the [package]``inter-server-sync`` package on "
"source and target servers."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/administration/pages/iss_v2.adoc:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "Content Synchronization"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: modules/administration/pages/iss_v2.adoc:8
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Export data on source server"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/iss_v2.adoc:9
msgid ""
"On the source server, on the command line execute the ISS export command.  "
"The [option]``-h`` option provides detailed help:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/iss_v2.adoc:10
#, no-wrap
msgid "inter-server-sync export -h\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/iss_v2.adoc:11
msgid ""
"The export procedure creates an output directory with all the needed data "
"for the import procedure."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: modules/administration/pages/iss_v2.adoc:12
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Copy export directory to target server"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/iss_v2.adoc:13
msgid ""
"Contents from the source server needs to be synchronized to the target "
"server.  On the command line, as root, execute:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/iss_v2.adoc:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "rsync -r <PATH_EXPORTED_DIR> root@<TARGET_SERVER>:~/\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/iss_v2.adoc:15
msgid "When all contents is copied, start importing it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: modules/administration/pages/iss_v2.adoc:16
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Import data on target server"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/iss_v2.adoc:17
msgid ""
"On the target server, on the command line execute the ISS import command.  "
"The [option]``-h`` option provides detailed help:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/iss_v2.adoc:18
#, no-wrap
msgid "inter-server-sync import -h\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/administration/pages/iss_v2.adoc:19
#, no-wrap
msgid "Database connection configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/iss_v2.adoc:20
msgid ""
"Database connection configuration is loaded by default from ``/etc/rhn/rhn."
"conf``.  Properties file location can be overridden with parameter ``--"
"serverConfig``."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/administration/pages/iss_v2.adoc:21
#, no-wrap
