#. type: Title ==
#: modules/administration/pages/removing-channels.adoc:2
#, no-wrap
msgid "Use Case"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/removing-channels.adoc:3
msgid ""
"This workflow shows how to manually remove {suse} provided channels from "
"{productname} and to clean up end-of-life products, to reclaim space or for "
"other purposes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/administration/pages/removing-channels.adoc:4
#, no-wrap
msgid "Step-by-step Instructions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/removing-channels.adoc:5
msgid ""
"Manual channel removal consists of <<preparing-to-remove-channel>> and "
"<<removing-channel>>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: modules/administration/pages/removing-channels.adoc:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "Preparing to Remove a Channel"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/removing-channels.adoc:7
msgid ""
"Before removing a channel, you must identify the label for the channel to be "
"removed.  It can be done with {webui} or on the command line."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/removing-channels.adoc:8
msgid ""
"Be careful not to remove channels that systems are currently subscribed to, "
