#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/troubleshooting/tshoot-disabling-fqdns-grain.adoc:5
msgid ""
"On the {productname} Server, at the command prompt, use this command to "
"disable the FQDNS grain:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/troubleshooting/tshoot-disabling-fqdns-grain.adoc:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "salt '*' state.sls util.mgr_disable_fqdns_grain\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/troubleshooting/tshoot-disabling-fqdns-grain.adoc:7
msgid ""
"This command restarts each client and generate Salt events that the server "
"needs to process.  If you have a large number of clients, you can execute "
"the command in batch mode instead:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/troubleshooting/tshoot-disabling-fqdns-grain.adoc:8
#, no-wrap
msgid "salt --batch-size 50 '*' state.sls util.mgr_disable_fqdns_grain\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/troubleshooting/tshoot-disabling-fqdns-grain.adoc:9
msgid ""
"Wait for the batch command to finish executing.  Do not interrupt the "
"process with kbd:[Ctrl+C]."
msgstr ""

