"single certificate.  If CDN presents a certificate that is different to the "
"one the {productname} {webui} knows about, validation fails and permission "
"to access the repository is denied, even though the certificate is "
"accurate.  The error message received is:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/troubleshooting/tshoot-rh-cdn-channel-and-multiple-certs.adoc:3
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[error]\n"
"Repository '<repo_name>' is invalid.\n"
"<repo.pem> Valid metadata not found at specified URL\n"
"History:\n"
" - [|] Error trying to read from '<repo.pem>'\n"
" - Permission to access '<repo.pem>' denied.\n"
"Please check if the URIs defined for this repository are pointing to a valid repository.\n"
"Skipping repository '<repo_nam' because of the above error.\n"
"Could not refresh the repositories because of errors.\n"
"HH:MM:SS RepoMDError: Cannot access repository. Maybe repository GPG keys are not imported\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/troubleshooting/tshoot-rh-cdn-channel-and-multiple-certs.adoc:4
msgid ""
"To resolve this issue, merge all valid certificates into a single ``.pem`` "
"file, and rebuild the certificates for use by {productname}:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: modules/administration/pages/troubleshooting/tshoot-rh-cdn-channel-and-multiple-certs.adoc:5
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Resolving Multiple {redhat} CDN Certificates"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/troubleshooting/tshoot-rh-cdn-channel-and-multiple-certs.adoc:6
msgid ""
"On the {redhat} client, at the command prompt, as root, gather all current "
"certificates from ``/etc/pki/entitlement/`` in a single ``rh-cert.pem`` file:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/troubleshooting/tshoot-rh-cdn-channel-and-multiple-certs.adoc:7
#, no-wrap
msgid "cat 866705146090697087.pem 3539668047766796506.pem redhat-entitlement-authority.pem > rh-cert.pem\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/troubleshooting/tshoot-rh-cdn-channel-and-multiple-certs.adoc:8
msgid ""
"Gather all current keys from ``/etc/pki/entitlement/`` in a single ``rh-key."
"pem`` file:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/troubleshooting/tshoot-rh-cdn-channel-and-multiple-certs.adoc:9
#, no-wrap
msgid "cat 866705146090697087-key.pem 3539668047766796506-key.pem > rh-key.pem\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/troubleshooting/tshoot-rh-cdn-channel-and-multiple-certs.adoc:10
msgid ""
"You can now import the new certificates to the {productname} Server, using "
"the instructions in xref:client-configuration:clients-rh-cdn.adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: modules/administration/pages/troubleshooting/tshoot-rpctimeout.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Troubleshooting RPC Connection Timeouts"
msgstr ""

#
#
#
#. PUT THIS COMMENT AT THE TOP OF TROUBLESHOOTING SECTIONS
#. Troubleshooting format:
#. One sentence each:
#. Cause: What created the problem?
#. Consequence: What does the user see when this happens?
#. Fix: What can the user do to fix this problem?
#. Result: What happens after the user has completed the fix?
#. If more detailed instructions are required, put them in a "Resolving" procedure:
#. .Procedure: Resolving Widget Wobbles
#. . First step
#. . Another step
#. . Last step
#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/troubleshooting/tshoot-rpctimeout.adoc:2
msgid ""
"RPC connections can sometimes time out due to slow networks or a network "
"link going down.  This results in package downloads or batch jobs hanging or "
"taking longer than expected.  You can adjust the maximum time that an RPC "
"connection can take by editing the configuration file.  While this does not "
"resolve networking problems, it does cause a process to fail rather than "
"hang."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: modules/administration/pages/troubleshooting/tshoot-rpctimeout.adoc:3
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Resolving RPC connection timeouts"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/troubleshooting/tshoot-rpctimeout.adoc:4
msgid ""
"On the {productname} Server, open the [filename]``/etc/rhn/rhn.conf`` file "
"and set a maximum timeout value (in seconds):"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/troubleshooting/tshoot-rpctimeout.adoc:5
#, no-wrap
msgid "server.timeout =`number`\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/troubleshooting/tshoot-rpctimeout.adoc:6
msgid ""
"On the {productname} Proxy, open the [filename]``/etc/rhn/rhn.conf`` file "
"and set a maximum timeout value (in seconds):"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/troubleshooting/tshoot-rpctimeout.adoc:7
#, no-wrap
msgid "proxy.timeout =`number`\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/troubleshooting/tshoot-rpctimeout.adoc:8
msgid ""
"On a {sles} client that uses zypper, open the [filename]``/etc/zypp/zypp."
"conf`` file and set a maximum timeout value (in seconds):"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/troubleshooting/tshoot-rpctimeout.adoc:9
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"## Valid values:  [0,3600]\n"
"## Default value: 180\n"
"download.transfer_timeout = 180\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/troubleshooting/tshoot-rpctimeout.adoc:10
msgid ""
"On a {rhel} client that uses yum, open the [filename]``/etc/yum.conf`` file "
"and set a maximum timeout value (in seconds):"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/troubleshooting/tshoot-rpctimeout.adoc:11
#, no-wrap
msgid "timeout =`number`\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/troubleshooting/tshoot-rpctimeout.adoc:12
msgid ""
"If you limit RPC timeouts to less than `180` seconds, you risk aborting "
"perfectly normal operations."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: modules/administration/pages/troubleshooting/tshoot-salt-clients-down-and-dns.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Troubleshooting Salt clients shown as down and DNS settings"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/troubleshooting/tshoot-salt-clients-down-and-dns.adoc:2
msgid ""
"Even if the Salt client is running, actions such as package refresh or apply "
"states can be marked as failed with the message:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/troubleshooting/tshoot-salt-clients-down-and-dns.adoc:3
#, no-wrap
msgid "Minion is down or could not be contacted.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/troubleshooting/tshoot-salt-clients-down-and-dns.adoc:4
msgid ""
"In this case try rescheduling the action.  If rescheduling succeeds, the "
"cause of the problem can be a wrong DNS configuration."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/troubleshooting/tshoot-salt-clients-down-and-dns.adoc:6
msgid ""
"When the Salt client is restarted, or in case the grains are refreshed, the "
"client calculates its FQDN grains, and it is unresponsive until the grains "
"are proceeded.  When a scheduled action on {productname} Server is going to "
"be executed, {productname} Server performs a ``test.ping`` to the client "
"before the actual action to ensure the client is actually running and the "
"action can be triggered."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/troubleshooting/tshoot-salt-clients-down-and-dns.adoc:7
msgid ""
"By default, {productname} Server waits for 5 seconds to get the response "
"from ``test.ping`` command.  If the response is not received within 5 "
"seconds, then the action is set to fail with the message that the client is "
"down or could not be contacted."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/troubleshooting/tshoot-salt-clients-down-and-dns.adoc:8
msgid ""
"To correct this, fix the DNS resolution on the client, so the client does "
"not get stuck for 5 seconds while solving its FQDN."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/troubleshooting/tshoot-salt-clients-down-and-dns.adoc:9
msgid ""
"If this is not possible, try to increase the value for ``java."
"salt_presence_ping_timeout`` in the ``/etc/rhn/rhn.conf`` file on the "
"{productname} Server to a value higher than 4."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/troubleshooting/tshoot-salt-clients-down-and-dns.adoc:11
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mgrctl term\n"
"vim /etc/rhn/rhn.conf\n"
"java.salt_presence_ping_timeout = 6\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/troubleshooting/tshoot-salt-clients-down-and-dns.adoc:12
msgid "After that, run:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/troubleshooting/tshoot-salt-clients-down-and-dns.adoc:14
msgid ""
"Increasing this value will cause {productname} Server to take longer to "
"check if a minion is unreachable or unresponsive, causing the {productname} "
"Server to be slower or less responsive overall."
msgstr ""

